03:56:43.810 --> 03:56:46.430
that Dr. King was talking about,

03:56:46.430 --> 03:56:49.010
that the Poor People's
Campaign was, was talking about,

03:56:49.010 --> 03:56:52.960
that poor people being the
Achilles heel of militarism,

03:56:52.960 --> 03:56:56.960
of racism, and of you know,
economic exploitation.

03:56:56.960 --> 03:56:59.830
But in our travels across
the country, as we were kind

03:56:59.830 --> 03:57:02.580
of calling for and
organizing this campaign,

03:57:02.580 --> 03:57:05.070
we found that in every
community that we went

03:57:05.070 --> 03:57:08.440
to that had poor folk,
there was some form

03:57:08.440 --> 03:57:09.750
of ecological devastation

03:57:09.750 --> 03:57:13.550
that was impacting those
people by far the most.

03:57:13.550 --> 03:57:16.300
And it became impossible
actually to talk

03:57:16.300 --> 03:57:19.420
about these issues without then
talking about the poisoning

03:57:19.420 --> 03:57:22.590
of water, the, the
extreme extraction,

03:57:22.590 --> 03:57:24.980
the fracking that's going on.

03:57:24.980 --> 03:57:28.340
And you know, the gas
incinerators being

03:57:28.340 --> 03:57:29.640
in poor communities.

03:57:29.640 --> 03:57:32.930
And so, so we said okay,
well we're going to learn

03:57:32.930 --> 03:57:35.010
from actually some of the
young people that were

03:57:35.010 --> 03:57:36.820
at Resurrection City in '68

03:57:36.820 --> 03:57:38.720
because there's some
amazing quotes.

03:57:38.720 --> 03:57:41.380
You know people date the
environmental movement

03:57:41.380 --> 03:57:43.950
to wait after the last '60s.

03:57:43.950 --> 03:57:47.320
