are doing the civil
disobedience,

04:01:43.700 --> 04:01:46.400
arm and arm with a Five
for Fifteen Worker.

04:01:46.400 --> 04:01:49.110
What it means it is that
they're, they're having the,

04:01:49.110 --> 04:01:51.710
the people in their
organizations figure

04:01:51.710 --> 04:01:55.280
out what it looks like to
actually work on a regular basis

04:01:55.280 --> 04:01:57.460
to build from the bottom
up in all the states

04:01:57.460 --> 04:01:58.940
that they have national
membership.

04:01:58.940 --> 04:02:04.070
And so, and so like what, what
we're seeing is, is you know,

04:02:04.070 --> 04:02:07.910
a flipping of the script,
where it's not that you have,

04:02:07.910 --> 04:02:12.700
you know, you know, big
important politicians

04:02:12.700 --> 04:02:15.060
or elected, or candidates
or, or other kind

04:02:15.060 --> 04:02:18.020
of known national leaders,
you have, you have the people

04:02:18.020 --> 04:02:19.320
who are coming together.

04:02:19.320 --> 04:02:24.610
And, but, and -- and then
another piece of, of history is

04:02:24.610 --> 04:02:30.680
that we are, are organizing
here in Washington DC.

04:02:30.680 --> 04:02:34.590
And it's happening in almost
40 states across the country.

04:02:34.590 --> 04:02:37.320
And what that looks
like is that you know,

04:02:37.320 --> 04:02:39.300
there are state coordinating
committees made

04:02:39.300 --> 04:02:42.820
up of a read diversity of
folks all across the country.

04:02:42.820 --> 04:02:47.420
And that we got from leaders
from '68, which was that,

04:02:47.420 --> 04:02:51.730
how do you build from the ground
up, how do you have an actual,

04:02:51.730 --> 04:02:54.790
you know, movement with
roots in the ground.

04:02:54.790 --> 04:02:59.090
Because where policies that
are being passed in particular

04:02:59.090 --> 04:03:03.160
that hurt people, that have
a long staying power is

04:03:03.160 --> 04:03:04.460
in people's state capitals.

04:03:04.460 --> 04:03:08.320
And so what does it look
like for us to, to you know,

04:03:08.320 --> 04:03:11.080
not say it's a national movement
because it has a P.O. Box

04:03:11.080 --> 04:03:13.660
in Washington DC, but
it's a national movement

04:03:13.660 --> 04:03:16.050
because we're nationalizing
state based

04:03:16.050 --> 04:03:17.780
and local based movements.

04:03:17.780 --> 04:03:20.760
And, and connecting them,
and, and building them out.

04:03:20.760 --> 04:03:25.320
And so, so you know
there's something,

04:03:25.320 --> 04:03:26.710
there's something going on and,

04:03:26.710 --> 04:03:30.700
and we want to invite folks
to, to be a part of that.

04:03:30.700 --> 04:03:34.200
Because what these 40
days have been is a launch

04:03:34.200 --> 04:03:37.360
of a first phase of a
Poor People's Campaign,

04:03:37.360 --> 04:03:39.160
and a national call
for moral revival.

04:03:39.160 --> 04:03:42.620
And, and what we've, what
we've seen is that people all

04:03:42.620 --> 04:03:48.110
across the country are,
are ready for a long fight.

04:03:48.110 --> 04:03:52.610
The, the problems of 140
million people being poor didn't

04:03:52.610 --> 04:03:53.910
happen overnight.

04:03:53.910 --> 04:03:56.100
The fact that there
are 37 million people

04:03:56.100 --> 04:03:58.640
without healthcare, that
didn't happen overnight.

04:03:58.640 --> 04:04:02.350
The fact that there are
four million households,

04:04:02.350 --> 04:04:05.070
when they turned on their water
this morning, there was lead

04:04:05.070 --> 04:04:07.550
in their water, like that
didn't happen overnight.

04:04:07.550 --> 04:04:09.920
So it's not going to
be overnight that all

04:04:09.920 --> 04:04:11.220
of those things are
going to change.

04:04:11.220 --> 04:04:13.470
It's going to need
a powerful movement,

04:04:13.470 --> 04:04:16.660
and I think we learned
this from history,

04:04:16.660 --> 04:04:19.070
and we learned this
from today, right.

04:04:19.070 --> 04:04:21.700
And so that, that
movement is happening.

04:04:21.700 --> 04:04:26.310
And so we, we've been traveling
around the country and kind

04:04:26.310 --> 04:04:28.190
of uniting and organizing folks.

04:04:28.190 --> 04:04:31.800
And, and I, I have been
particularly inspired by this,

04:04:31.800 --> 04:04:37.850
this one quote from Dr. King,
from the Massy Lectures in '67

04:04:37.850 --> 04:04:41.380
when he kind of was calling for
and putting out some of the,

04:04:41.380 --> 04:04:44.160
the ideas of the Poor
People's Campaign.

04:04:44.160 --> 04:04:46.990
And he says, there is nothing
wrong with a traffic light

04:04:46.990 --> 04:04:50.090
which says that you have
to stop for a red light,

04:04:50.090 --> 04:04:53.490
but when a fire is raging,
the fire truck goes right

04:04:53.490 --> 04:04:54.940
through that red light,

04:04:54.940 --> 04:04:58.490
and normal traffic had
better get out of its way.

04:04:58.490 --> 04:05:03.220
Or when a man is bleeding
to death, the ambulance goes

04:05:03.220 --> 04:05:07.090
through those red
lights at top speed.

04:05:07.090 --> 04:05:11.960
There is a fire raging now
for the poor of this society.

04:05:11.960 --> 04:05:13.810
They are living in
tragic conditions

04:05:13.810 --> 04:05:16.090
because the terrible
economic injustices

04:05:16.090 --> 04:05:19.140
that keep them locked in.

04:05:19.140 --> 04:05:23.360
Disinherited people all over
the world are bleeding to death

04:05:23.360 --> 04:05:26.490
from deep social
and economic wounds.

04:05:26.490 --> 04:05:30.070
They need for gabs of
ambulance drivers who will have

04:05:30.070 --> 04:05:33.430
to ignore the red light
of the present system

04:05:33.430 --> 04:05:36.390
until the emergency is solved.

04:05:36.390 --> 04:05:40.530
Massive civil disobedience is
a strategy for social change,

04:05:40.530 --> 04:05:43.880
which is at least as
forceful as an ambulance

04:05:43.880 --> 04:05:46.270
with its sirens on full.

04:05:46.270 --> 04:05:50.550
And so what we have all across
the country is thousands

04:05:50.550 --> 04:05:54.810
of ambulance drivers, thousands
of people who have signed

04:05:54.810 --> 04:05:58.770
up to say that they will
ignore the red lights of racism

04:05:58.770 --> 04:06:02.210
and sexism and poverty
and militarism

04:06:02.210 --> 04:06:06.040
and ecological devastation
and that they will,

04:06:06.040 --> 04:06:10.670
they will continue to do this
until the emergency is solved.

04:06:10.670 --> 04:06:16.020
And that you know, to, to go
back and think about the role

04:06:16.020 --> 04:06:19.350
that nonviolent civil
disobedience has in history,

04:06:19.350 --> 04:06:23.460
the role of poor people
coming together and, and,

04:06:23.460 --> 04:06:29.230
and disrupting and calling
to account the structures

04:06:29.230 --> 04:06:31.770
that are impoverishing,
the structures

04:06:31.770 --> 04:06:40.940
that are killing people
and, and to say not today.

04:06:40.940 --> 04:06:43.970
Not on our watch.

04:06:43.970 --> 04:06:50.040
And in such a time as this
we are called indeed to,

04:06:50.040 --> 04:06:54.810
to organize, we are called
to mobilize, we are called

04:06:54.810 --> 04:06:59.020
to educate, we are called to
celebrate, and we are called to,

04:06:59.020 --> 04:07:01.710
to build a powerful movement.

04:07:01.710 --> 04:07:07.000
And so we invite everybody
to be a part of this.

04:07:07.000 --> 04:07:09.830
We need everyone.

04:07:09.830 --> 04:07:11.740
Especially the people that are.

04:07:11.740 --> 04:07:16.230
And all roads at this point,
because we're on week five,

04:07:16.230 --> 04:07:21.920
lead to week six, and lead to
June 23rd where at 7th Street

04:07:21.920 --> 04:07:26.850
